<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Anchor2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Anchor,</orth> subst., iron instrument to hold a ship at rest: <cit><quote>the a. is deep,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 56</bibl></cit> (it is cast out and holds). <cit><quote>to make his a. hold,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 213</bibl></cit>. <emph>it came home,</emph> 214, i. e. it was dislodged from its bed. <cit><quote>nothing so certain as your --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.581" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 581</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 4, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 4, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.26" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 4, 38</bibl>. <cit><quote>at a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>